%%{init: {'theme': 'default', 'sequence': {'actorFontSize': 22, 'actorFontWeight': 'bold', 'messageFontSize': 20, 'noteFontSize': 18, 'mirrorActors': false, 'actorMargin': 60, 'boxMargin': 12, 'messageMargin': 40, 'wrap': true}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor User
    participant UI
    participant IdP as HMCTS IdP / mock-auth
    participant Svc as Any ram service
    participant Authz as ram-authorisation

    rect rgb(232, 240, 250)
        Note over User,Authz: Phase 1 — Login + JWT issuance
        User->>UI: open RAM Pathfinder app
        UI->>IdP: OIDC authorization_code request
        User->>IdP: authenticate via SSO
        IdP-->>UI: redirect with authorization code
        UI->>IdP: exchange code for JWT
        IdP-->>UI: short-lived JWT signed by IdP
    end

    rect rgb(232, 250, 232)
        Note over User,Authz: Phase 2 — Per-service JWT validation against JWKS
        Note right of UI: Every subsequent API call carries the JWT as Bearer. APIM is on the path but omitted for clarity.
        UI->>Svc: API call with Bearer JWT
        Svc->>IdP: GET /.well-known/jwks.json (cached)
        IdP-->>Svc: JWKS public keys
        Svc->>Svc: validate signature and expiry
    end

    rect rgb(250, 240, 230)
        Note over User,Authz: Phase 3 — Per-request authz check + activation gating
        Svc->>Authz: POST /authz/check with principal and endpoint
        Authz->>Authz: resolve identity — email to personnel number (jo_people) or staff UUID (ram_auth_staff_identities)
        Authz->>Authz: resolve roles, jurisdiction, Region/Area scope, activation flag per FR57
        alt principal resolved, activated for the wave, and authorised
            Authz-->>Svc: allowed — returns canonical id, roles, jurisdiction, scope
            Svc->>Svc: populate AuthDetails request-scoped bean
            Svc-->>UI: controller runs, 2xx response
        else unresolvable, not activated, or not authorised
            Authz-->>Svc: denied
            Svc-->>UI: 403 Forbidden with RFC 9457 problem-details
        end
    end

    Note over User,Authz: Every other sequence diagram assumes this flow has already run on the inbound call. Service-to-service calls forward the user JWT, and Phase 2 + 3 happen at each hop.
